file_name: File:79th anniversary of the outbreak of World War II. Speaker of the Sejm, Marek Kuchciński, makes a wreath on the graves of Polish soldiers.jpg
description: [None]
parsed caption:
The Speaker of the Sejm, Marek Kuchciński, makes a wreath on the graves of
Polish soldiers, defenders of the Polish Westerplatte. Westerplatte. Poland.
Celebration of the 79th anniversary of the outbreak of World War II with the
participation of the Marshal of the Sejm. On September 1, 1939, Nazi Germany
invaded Poland. World War II began. On September 17, 1939, Soviet Russia
attacked Poland from the east. Ribbentrop - Molotov Pact of August 23, 1939
with a secret annex. Hitler's Germany and Stalin's Russia, two dictatorial
states invaded Poland. The fourth partition of Poland took place, between
Hitler's Nazi Germany and Stalin's Soviet Russia.

file_name: File:The West of Cornwall Primary Care Trust (Establishment) Order 2001 (UKSI 2001-1175 qp).pdf
depicts: ['The West of Cornwall Primary Care Trust (Establishment) Order 2001']
description: ['UK Statutory Instrument 2001\xa0No. 1175']
parsed caption:
This Order establishes the West of Cornwall Primary Care Trust (“the trust”),
as provided for under section 16A of the National Health Service Act 1977. It
specifies the area for which the trust is established (article 3 and the
Schedule), its operational date (article 5) and limitations on the exercise of
its functions during its preparatory period (article 6). It makes provision
for the membership of the trust (article 4) and for assistance to the trust
during its preparatory period (article 7).

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0335 channel (as well as AIA 211) highlights the active region of the
outer atmosphere of the Sun - the corona. Active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - or coronal
holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the main
source of solar wind particles.  
  
**Where:** Active regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 335 angstroms (0.0000000335 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 15 times ionized iron (Fe XVI)

**Characteristic temperature:** 2.8 million K (5 million F)

file_name: File:NYCT Customer Service Center Opens by Appointment Only with COVID Protections (50091056098).jpg
description: ['most populous city in the United States', 'Wikimedia disambiguation page']
parsed caption:
The Metropolitan Transportation Authority announced that after a pause to put
COVID protections in place during the recent pandemic, the walk-in NYC Transit
Customer Service Center in Lower Manhattan has reopened, by appointment only.
The Center is an accessible location for customers to receive information and
assistance for various matters related to NYC Transit services. There are now
numerous COVID-19 protections in place for both MTA employees and customers,
including a thermal scanning temperature device, plexiglass barriers,
sanitizer and social distancing guidelines in the waiting room and at service
windows.

Photo: Marc A. Hermann / MTA New York City Transit

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 1700 channel (as well as AIA 1600) often shows a web-like pattern of
bright areas that highlight places where bundles of magnetic fields lines are
concentrated. However, small areas with a lot of field lines will appear
black, usually near sunspots and active regions.

**Where:** Temperature minimum and photosphere

**Wavelength:** 1700 angstroms (0.00000017 m) = Far Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** Continuum

**Characteristic temperature:** 6,000 K (11,000 F)

description: ['Roman amphitheatre in Nîmes, France']
parsed caption:
The Arena of Nîmes is a Roman amphitheatre, situated in the French city of
Nîmes. Built around AD 70, it was remodelled in 1863 to serve as a bullring.  
  
The Arena of Nîmes is the site of two annual bullfights during the Feria de
Nîmes, and it is also used for other public events. The arena served as a
public event theatre built by the Romans as well as a gladiator fighting
arena.

The building encloses an elliptical central space 133 m long by 101 m wide. It
is ringed by 34 rows of seats supported by a vaulted construction. It has a
capacity of 24,000 spectators and since 1989 has a movable cover and a heating
system [Wikipedia.org]

description: ['Soviet major general']
parsed caption:
Lot 8988-20 (SC-111-27266): Surrender of Germany, 7 May 1945. Terms of
Unconditional Surrender are here being dictated to the Representatives of the
German government in the War Room of Supreme Headquarters, Allied
Expeditionary Forces (SHAEF), at Reims, France. In the picture, backs to
camera, are Major Wilhelm Oxenius, of the German General Staff; (nearest
camera) Colonel General Gustaf Jodl, German Chief of Staff; General Admiral
Von Friedburg, of the German Navy, facing the camera on the far side of the
table, seated are (left to right) Lieutenant General Sir F. E. Morgan, Deputy
Chief of Staff; General Francois Sevez, Representative of General Alphonse
Juin, French Chief of Staff; Admiral Harold M. Burrough, Commander in Chief,
Allied Naval Expeditionary Forces; Lieutenant General W.B. Smith, Chief of
Staff, SHAEF; and Major General of Artillery Ivan Alexeyevich Susloparov,
Russian Representative. Standing behind General Sevez is Captain H.C. Butcher,
Naval Aide to General Eisenhower. U.S. Army Photograph. (2015/10/16).

**Identificatie**  
**Titel(s):** Natuurhistorische ensemble (nr. 12)12. Blad van Mengelmoes.
Miscelaniorum tabula 12.. 12. feuille de melange (titel op object)  
**Objecttype:** tekening  
**Objectnummer:** RP-T-BR-2017-1-7-41  
**Omschrijving:** Blad met de twaalfde natuurhistorische ensemble met dieren
en planten, nummers 1-17. Insecten (vlinders, vliegen, kevers, libel), kikker,
slak, vruchten en bloemen. Genummerd rechtsboven: 12. Onderdeel van het
zevende album met tekeningen van reptielen, amfibieën en natuurhistorische
ensembles. Het zevende van twaalf albums met aquarellen van dieren, vogels en
planten bekend rond 1600, gemaakt in opdracht van keizer Rudolf II. Met
toelichting in Nederlands, Latijn en Frans.  
  
**Vervaardiging**  
**Vervaardiger:** tekenaar: Elias Verhulst (toegeschreven aan), tekenaar:
Anselmus Boëtius de Boodt (mogelijk), naar prent van: Jacob Hoefnagel  
**Plaats vervaardiging:** tekenaar: Delft, tekenaar: Praag  
**Datering:** 1596 - 1610  
**Fysieke kenmerken:** penseel in waterverf en dekverf in kleuren over potlood
of zwart krijt, gehoogd met witte dekverf, handschrift in pen in bruin  
**Materiaal:** papier potlood krijt waterverf dekverf inkt  
**Techniek:** penseel / pen  
**Afmetingen:** blad: h 192 mm × b 268 mm  
  
**Onderwerp**

A round-bottom flask with the solid to be analyzed A is digested with sodium
hydroxide and connected to a wide glass spiral B and a vertical condenser C.
The system is cooled through the network R, H, E, F and G. By collecting the
ammoniacal distillate in a beaker D with a known excess of acid, it is
possible to determine the nitrogen content as ammoniacal nitrogen.

description: ['actor (1893-1979)', '1940 film by Anders Henrikson']
parsed caption:
** _Terrassen:_ Ett brott**  
[Sigfrid Siwertz](https://sv.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sigfrid_Siwertz "sv:Sigfrid
Siwertz") skådespel "[Ett brott](https://sv.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ett_brott
"sv:Ett brott")" i [Anders
Henriksons](https://sv.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anders_Henrikson_\(sk%C3%A5despelare\)
"sv:Anders Henrikson \(skådespelare\)") filmåtergivning från 1940 brukar
betecknas som inkörsporten till andra storhetstiden i svensk produktion, det
verk som inledde en på samma gång stramare och djärvare dramatisk linje efter
1930-talets mer lösliga periodHur verkar det då idag, 16 år efteråt? Alltjämt
starkt, framför allt i kraft av styckets laddade intrig, dess familjetragedi
och kriminaldramatik, dess tacksamma spelscener och psykologiskt intressanta
persongalleri. "Ett brott" är och förblir en storartat välspelad ensamblefilm
och ger dessutom en ovanligt accentuerad miljöskildring. Stämningen i det
stränga justitierådshemmet lägger sig som en tyngd över bröstet. Naturligtvis
ger nypremiären en klar bild av hur filmtekniken har marscherat fram under tre
luster.  
Svenska Dagbladet 15/5 1956.

![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Info_non-
talk.svg/15px-Info_non-talk.svg.png)

Phil Stacey sings “Blaze of Glory” for approximately 850 Student Life children
at Lee University during Navy Week Chattanooga. Navy Week Chattanooga runs
June 8-17. Navy weeks are designed to show American’s the investment they have

significant Navy presence. U.S. Navy photo by Mass Communication Specialist

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
HMI measures the Sun's magnetic field over the entire visible disk with 1 arc
second resolution. The line of sight magnetic field color table is designed to
visually show structure at both high and low field values.

Field strengths <24 G are shades of gray. Positive Field Values are green and
blue. Negative field values are yellow and red.

Weak field regions appear mostly yellow or green. Increasingly positive values
range from dark green to bright green at 236G. Negative values move from
bright yellow to orange at -236G.

There is a sharp discontinuity in color at 236G.

Positive or negative polarity sunspots and other strong field regions will
appear blue or red with dark umbrae.

There are 254 defined colors symmetrically arranged around the zero point.

The 127 positive include 2 darkening gray, 18 brightening green, and 110
darkening blue.

The 127 negative include 2 brightening gray, 18 darkening yellow, and 107
darkening red.

Nominally, each color spans a range of ~11.81 G and the color table extends
from -1500 to 1500 G.

  *[![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Info_non-talk.svg/15px-Info_non-talk.svg.png)]: Files from the inventories “Bild 101 Propagandakompanien der Wehrmacht” and “Bild 183 ADN” may have particularly biased or politically extreme descriptions.

file_name: File:BCN lanza Programa Ley Fácil y Leyes en Mapudungun (3215634661).jpg
description: ['Chilean politician (1943-2013)']
parsed caption:
BCN lanza Programa Ley Fácil y Leyes en Mapudungun

Los presidentes del Senado, Adolfo Zaldívar, y de la Cámara de Diputados,
Francisco Encina, encabezaron este 21 de enero el lanzamiento oficial del
Programa Ley Fácil, de la Biblioteca del Congreso Nacional (BCN), destinado a
hacer accesible las leyes a la ciudadanía usando un lenguaje de fácil
entendimiento y cotidiano.

La BCN se ha propuesto ser un puente entre el origen de las leyes y la
ciudadanía y en cumplimiento de este objetivo empezó a desarrollar hace un par
de años un proyecto que pusiera las leyes al alcance de toda la ciudadanía,
pero que pese al uso de un lenguaje claro y muy accesible, fueran precisas
desde el punto de vista jurídico. Se comenzó con las leyes de más alta demanda
ciudadana, hasta completar 100 el año pasado y se dio comienzo a la difusión
gratuita.

Mas información en:

[www.bcn.cl/noticias/bcn-lanza-programa-ley-facil-y-
leyes-...](http://www.bcn.cl/noticias/bcn-lanza-programa-ley-facil-y-leyes-en-
mapudungun)

file_name: File:A U.S. Army UH-60 Black Hawk helicopter assigned to the Colorado Army National Guard picks up water for a water drop while fighting the Black Forest Fire near Colorado Springs, Colo., June 12, 2013 130612-Z-UA373-074.jpg
description: ['perennial woody plant']
parsed caption:
A U.S. Army UH-60 Black Hawk helicopter assigned to the Colorado Army National
Guard picks up water for a water drop while fighting the Black Forest Fire
near Colorado Springs, Colo., June 12, 2013. The Black Hawks, which were sent
from the Army Aviation Support Facility at Buckley Air Force Base in Aurora,
Colo., performed the water drops using helicopter buckets that could carry up
to 500 gallons of water. The Black Hawks could make more than 20 drops before
refueling. The Black Forest Fire started June 11, 2013, northeast of Colorado
Springs, burning scores of homes and forcing large-scale evacuations. The
Colorado National Guard and U.S. Air Force Reserve assisted in firefighting
efforts.

Mullen visits with Vietnamese Deputy Minister of National Defense, Senior Lt.

description: ['metro station on Line B of Buenos Aires underground']
parsed caption:
Bahnsteig stadtauswärts, Blickrichtung West. Die Linie B wurde ursprünglich
mit von oben bestrichener Stromschiene nach denselben Maßen wie die »Línea
Urquiza« nach General Lemos ausgerüstet, doch für den Einsatz der aus Madrid
übernommenen Reihen CAF 5000 und 6000 mussten 2013 zusätzlich Fahrleitungen,
zumeist in Form von Deckenstromschienen, eingebaut werden. Vor dem
Bahnsteigende liegt eine Fahrleitungstrennstelle. Die Gleise liegen auf
Zweiblockbetonschwellen mit Pandrol-Spannklemmen.

  *[![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Info_non-talk.svg/15px-Info_non-talk.svg.png)]: Files from the inventories “Bild 101 Propagandakompanien der Wehrmacht” and “Bild 183 ADN” may have particularly biased or politically extreme descriptions.

file_name: File:The Dogger Bank Teesside A and B Offshore Wind Farm (Amendment) Order 2021 (UKSI 2021-39).pdf
depicts: ['The Dogger Bank Teesside A and B Offshore Wind Farm (Amendment) Order 2021']
description: ['UK Statutory Instrument 2021\xa0No. 39']
parsed caption:
This Order amends The Teesside A and B Offshore Wind Farm Order 2015, a
development consent order under the Planning Act 2008, following an
application made in accordance with the Infrastructure Planning (Changes to,
and Revocation of, Development Consent Orders) Regulations 2011 for a non-
material change under paragraph 2 of Schedule 6 to the Planning Act 2008. The
Order amends the limits on hammer energy during installation and makes some
changes to the cabling descriptions within the array.

parsed caption:
Papageno-Statue zum Gedenken an [Hermann
Prey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/de:Hermann_Prey "w:de:Hermann Prey"),
Papagenoplatz, Krailling. Eine Plakette informiert:

    

    **Der Vogelfänger bin ich ja  
Zum Gedenken an Kammersänger  
Hermann Prey  
1929–1998  
von seiner Familie  
Bildhauerin: Johanna Körner – 82152 Krailling**

Der _Papageno_ (in Mozarts _Die Zauberflöte_) war eine der bedeutenden
Opernrollen in der Karriere des Sängers. – Die kleine Statue wirkt nicht
monumental, nicht platzbeherrschend und knüpft stilistisch etwa an Werke von
Renée Sintenis an.

description: ['preserved American 2-8-2 locomotive (D&RGW K-28 class)']
parsed caption:
Photo of Denver and Rio Grand narrow gauge locomotive 476 (2-8-2) on an
excursion at Silverton, Colorado, May 30, 1954. The photo was taken by noted
railroad photographer [en:Otto Perry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Otto_Perry
"en:Otto Perry"). Perry earned his living as a mailman in Denver;
photographing trains was a hobby he pursued for many years. Perry was also
known to travel outside of the Denver area to photograph trains.

Like many other railfans who take photos, Perry had prints made up as
postcards and used a ink stamp to identify their work as these photos were
shared with others who also had a hobby of photographing trains.

Perry died in 1970, leaving his collection of train photos and negatives to
the Denver Public Library.

  *[![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Info_non-talk.svg/15px-Info_non-talk.svg.png)]: Files from the inventories “Bild 101 Propagandakompanien der Wehrmacht” and “Bild 183 ADN” may have particularly biased or politically extreme descriptions.
